1. What is Power BI?
Answer:
Power BI is a Business Intelligence (BI) and Data Visualization tool developed by Microsoft. It helps users analyze data, create interactive reports, and build dashboards for better business decisions.
________________________________________
2. What is Power BI used for?
Answer:
Power BI is used for:
•	Data Analysis 
•	Creating Interactive Dashboards 
•	Generating Reports 
•	Tracking Sales and Profit 
•	Monitoring Business Performance 
•	Visualizing Data using Charts and Graphs 
________________________________________
3. What are the main components of Power BI?
Answer:
•	Power BI Desktop 
•	Power BI Service 
•	Power BI Mobile App 
•	Power BI Gateway 
•	Power BI Report Server 
________________________________________
4. What is Power BI Desktop?
Answer:
Power BI Desktop is a free application used to connect data sources, transform data, and create reports and dashboards.
________________________________________
5. What is the difference between a Dashboard and a Report?
Answer:
Dashboard	Report
Single page	Multiple pages
Displays summary information	Provides detailed analysis
Contains visuals from one or more reports	Contains multiple visualizations
________________________________________
6. Which data sources can Power BI connect to?
Answer:
Power BI can connect to:
•	Excel 
•	SQL Server 
•	MySQL 
•	Oracle Database 
•	CSV Files 
•	SharePoint 
•	Web 
•	Azure 
•	Google Analytics 
•	Salesforce 
________________________________________
7. What is a visualization in Power BI?
Answer:
A visualization is a graphical representation of data, such as charts, tables, maps, and graphs, used to make data easier to understand.
________________________________________
8. What is DAX?
Answer:
DAX (Data Analysis Expressions) is a formula language used in Power BI to create calculated columns, measures, and calculated tables.
